wdi2-SH.DYN.0509.def: Probability of dying between age 5-9 years of age expressed per 1,000 children aged 5, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of the specified year.
wdi2-SH.DYN.0509.name: Probability of dying among children ages 5-9 years
wdi2-SH.DYN.0509.source: Estimates developed by the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (UNICEF, WHO, World Bank, UN DESA Population Division) at www.childmortality.org.
